tip.text: This is brunch food at its finest. If u're gonna fork out $20 for smashed avo or hash or pancakes, make sure u do it here.
Affordable Chinese fare. Recommended: fried fish head/sliced fish noodles, loh mai fun, wonton noodles and fish porridge
U're here partially cos of The NY Times. U're queuing maybe cos it's FOMO. Take a step back. Screw 'em expectations & appreciate the croissants, kouign amman & cruffins just as they are. Rmb to enjoy
Best and cutest-looking cuppa piccolo I've had in a long while. Serves beans from Melbourne-based roasters Axil and homegrown Nylon.

formattedAddress: China Square Foodcourt (51 Telok Ayer St)

tip.text: The Signature Vegan Bowls here are just the tastiest good-looking scraps of sliced and puréed vegetables and complex carbs ever assembled in bowls. I feel like my ethics score has jumped fivefolds
It's a decent bowl of rice with pork and some green peas. If u're in the area, and u are not in the mood for ramen, this is worth a try. Not something that U'd brave the storms and seas to have.
Cool vibe, interesting entry, friendly service, lots of seating (rooftop recommended!), hearty ramens, delicious baos!
Had high hopes for the butter sauces but the food is just ok.. doesn't shine. There's nothing truly unique about the food.. with the plethora of options around, it's hard to say you'll surely return.
If u're here solely for hearty Mexican staples such as burrito, chili con carne, stuffed jalapeños, tacos and chimichanga, u will be utterly delighted. So so so tasty.
Pair your ice cream with the scones!
Paella is so good and so tasty. Enough to feed 6-7 (the guys here will say 4) if you're ordering other dishes as well.
You can't leave without trying the boysenberry pie. Great that it's not sweet. The berry fillings have a fragrance like tea and the dough is soft.

If u hav anti-carb friends, u might b able to turn their world around with the signature rice here. Simply outta this world. Never mind the salted duck egg, truffle yakini..saywhat, just eat the rice!
Rice meals are very savoury but delicious. Cuisine seems more fusion than Japanese as the dishes are really rich and toppings-heavy. Not on the cheap end.

venue.name: Sun With Moon Japanese Dining & Café

tip.text: Yam duck and deep fried beancurd were my fav dishes here. Nice ambience and good service.
Coconut poached fish x spiced squash - Interesting play on flavors. Prawn x masala dressing was refreshing. Choc fritters & ginger ice cream surprisingly work well tgt. But waiting time was dismal.

formattedAddress: Marina Bay Sands Hotel Tower 2 (Bayfront Avenue)

tip.text: This Alaskan king crab ravioli is lipsmackin' tasty and addictive. Love the texture of the garnish and crunch from the crab. The bisque is awesome too. Only thing is that the ravioli is too thick
One of the most balanced piccolos I've had. Now u probably wonder wtf balanced is. For me it's a combination of bitterness, acidity & sweetness from the milk. Ok getting off my coffee high horse✌🏼️
Truffle fries with kelp and some awesome cheese shavings
Still not sure what "fried rice chicken"is as there's nary a grain of rice there but it's fuckin good. And the spicy sauced up versions are so fiery hot and delicious u won't know when to stop

formattedAddress: Level 2 Hong Leong Building (16 Raffles Quay)

tip.text: Pricey stuff.
The standard fare is pretty boring but the Aging cheese selections are a different story. Worth a try.
Here I m tryin to rmb the taste of that awesome squid+broccolini+nuts dish, but all I can think of is the fragrant flower/tea cake that I don't know the name of. Well played guys.
Here for dinner. Must-try: salmon tiradito (amazing mix of flavors, will amuse u), fried aubergine w yogurt (refreshingly good) and cacao truffles w chilli (fuckin awesome, beware it's pretty spicy)
Not exactly the place to go if you're starving. Yes it's ciccheti, but my disappointment was thru the roof when the ravioli that arrived was nothing more than 3 pieces of stuffed dough.
Eggs Benny on smashed avo toast with bacon was not bad at all. Standard good stuff that your belly loves.
Portion is good for sharing. Good value. Love the pasta. Limited wine selection tho.
Clams in white wine was our favorite dish. Seafood here is so fresh it's shocking. What have I been eating all my life!
Fantastic service and tasty seafood. Portions are huge so feel free to share. The garlic shrimps (gambas) appetizer is easily a winner. Wash them all down with a white from Casa Ermelinda.
The pastries (sweet and savoury) were too good to be true. Order the flat pastry with cheese and ham, the one with pumpkin in it, and whatever else you fancy. Everything is awesome. No kiddin
Their mains shine but make sure there's space for desserts. The carrot walnut cake with cream cheese and chocolate cake with rum were one the best ones I've ever had.
Love the sourdough pizzas. Try the "less-tomato" or "no tomato" ones to let the sourdough taste come through even more.
The broth was light and rich at the same time it's uncanny. Ramens in Asia are shockingly salty and fatty but the London ones are just so balanced. Ok the chashu was fatty but my face wanted it.
How do you summarize a 3-hour meal made and served by a team of dedicated talented culinary maestros right in front of you? An explosion of amazingness. I died and woke up in gastro heaven.
Fish head noodle soup
One of the best ciders I've ever had. Love the crisp taste and the fact that it's non-gaseous! Remember to bring home some ciders!
Reasonably clean. Offers tasty and cheap shakes (almond peanut butter - served cold thick and creamy) Juices are great too - ask for no ice!
The chicken masala was okay. The toasts were simply comforting if u need an alternative to chapati and basmati rice.
Deep fried vege momos = piping hot goodness.
Awesome protein smoothie. It's actually called Protein Smoothie. You can ask them to exclude the spinach if you think it's too weird.
Fantastic brioche though pricey.
No-frills Indonesian cuisine in a comfortable (rather upmarket) setting. Wallet-friendly though!

formattedAddress: Kawasan Pariwisata Nusa Dua BTDC Area lot C-0

tip.text: Fresh fruits and carbs and sugar and uhh superfoods? Addictive. And damn good on a hot day - which is everyday.
This is THE Awesome dish I was looking for in Bali. Smashed Avo on toasted sourdough. Bursting with flavors. Egg perfectly poached too.

tip.text: Affordable fresh fruit juice-shake concoctions! Try this dragon fruit x banana shake. Muy delicious!
Sunday jams. Mix of English and Bahasa songs. Get a Rp50.000 sangria and lounge on the picnic mat or if u're a ladder person, go find a cozy corner.
Pastas are al Dente perfection and flavors are spot on. I always finish with a tiramisu whenever I do Italian & this one doesn't disappoint - nice touch with the choc chips at the bottom!

tip.text: The savory beef patty combined with the sweetness of the bacon jam, zestiness of the Granny Smiths, and cheesy goodness of the, well, cheese.. is pure gold. Praise the Lard indeed!
Burgers are nubbad. I'd come here for the peanut butter shakes if I'm batshit depressed and need a quickjoy solution.
Pho broth is on the sweet side, tasty nonetheless. Broken rice and pad Thai are worth the calories 😆
The truffle risotto is a 🦄. Divine in taste & fragrance, do enquire if they still have it on cos it's a "special" when we were there. Homemade ciabatta with cheese is also an underrated stunner👍🏼

Love the sweetness & savoriness of the pork burger. The shakes are pretty inventive too. And thumbs up for their healthy options + the friendly staff makes the dining experience all the more pleasant.
For an explosion of flavors get the pork noodles. And you've got to have them with their homemade chilli with lime. I also heard the wonton mee from a neighboring stall is fantastic.

tip.text: That lemon tart and basil ice cream is straight out of foodgasmland. There's also that pork collar cooked to perfection. And crab pappardelle in Thai curry - simply 👏🏽. I'm coming back for more.
You're won't be able to avoid mutton stew, mutton dumplings, mutton with rice, mutton everything in UB. Pls be reminded the smell is very potent, the taste - very strong.
